<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">

  <head>

    <title>CSS Backgrounds and Borders Test: border-radius - inheritance</title>
    <link rel="author" title="GÃ©rard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/" />
    <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-background/#the-border-radius" title="5.1. Curve Radii: the 'border-radius' properties" />
    <link rel="match" href="reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square.xht" />
    <meta name="flags" content="" />
    <meta name="assert" content="This test checks that 'border-radius' property is not inherited by default." />

    <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
    div#overlapped-red
    {
    background-color: red;
    height: 100px;
    position: absolute;
    width: 100px;       
    z-index: -1; 
    }

    div#parent /* div#parent is overlapping div#overlapped-red */
    {
    border: transparent solid 25px; 
    border-radius: 50px;
    bottom: 25px;
    height: 50px;
    position: relative;
    right: 25px;
    width: 50px;
    }

    div#child
    {
    background-color: green;   
    border: green solid 25px;
    height: 50px;
    width: 50px;
    }
    ]]></style>
  </head>
  <body>

    <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>

    <div id="overlapped-red"></div>

    <div id="parent">
      <div id="child"></div>
    </div>

  </body>
</html>
